items.details: Home baked goodness. Just add water. No hydrogenated oils. Certified Organic by G.O.C.A. USDA organic.
items.directions: You Will Need: 1 Marie Callender's Corn Bread pouch and 1-1/2 cups water. 1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Grease or spray sides on bottom of 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan or muffin cups. 2. Add 1-1/2 cups of water into mixing bowl. 3. Blend contents of package with water until all lumps disappear (about 20 strokes). Do not overmix. 4. Pour batter into prepared pan or scoop into muffin cups. Bake immediately. 5. Bake bread at 375 degrees F for 30-35 minutes. Bake muffins at 375 degrees F for 20-25 minutes. High altitude baking instructions (above 5,000 Ft): Add 1 Tbsp. all-purpose flour and 2 Tbsp. of water. For convection ovens, reduce time by 5 minutes and temperature by 25 degrees.

items.directions: What You Need: 1/2 cup warm water, 2/3 cup oil, 1 egg. Prep: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Grease metal baking pan lightly. Mix: Combine in a medium bowl; mix, warm water & oil. Stir by hand until well blended. Beat egg and then add to bowl. Stir until batter is smooth. Bake: Pour batter into 8 inch x 8 inch square metal baking pan. Bake approximately 45-55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. High Altitude: Add 1 tbsp of flour to dry mix. Bake as directed. For vegan baking instructions please visit madhavasweeteners.com. Try These Variations: Do you love a more cake-y brownie? Add 2 eggs instead of one. Proceed as directed. Sometimes you feel like a nut. Add 1 cup of walnuts to prepared batter.

items.directions: You will need: 1 pan (8 inches); 2 large eggs; 6 tbsp of butter, melted and cooled. Note: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Grease the bottom and sides of an 8 inch x 8 inch square baking pan. 1. Mix it up! Beat eggs with an electric mixer on high speed for 2 minutes. Fold in mix. Stir just to moisten. Add melted and cooled butter. Beat on low medium speed until smooth. 2. Spread it around! Pour batter into preheated pan. 3. Bake it up! Bake at 350 degrees for 28-32 min. Brownies are done when a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan. Cool completely before cutting into squares. Enjoy!

items.directions: Note: Place plastic wrap on surface of warm pudding to prevent skin formation! You Will Need: 2 cups milk (preferably whole milk). 1 egg yolk (well beaten), optional. Baking: Combine pudding mix and milk in a small sauce pan. Stir well to dissolve mixture. Cook over med low heat, stirring constantly. Bring mixture to boil, cook and stir for an additional minute before removing from heat. Pour pudding into 4 serving dishes. Refrigerate at least 90 minutes. For extra creamy, smooth pudding, add 1 well beaten egg yolk to the dissolved mixture and follow the cooking instructions above.

items.name: Doughs, Gelatins & Bake Mixes Pamela's Cornbread & Muffin Mix
items.display_name: Pamela's Cornbread & Muffin Mix
items.directions: Pamela's Sweet Old Fashioned Cornbread: 1 bag Pamela's Mix; 1/2 cup sugar; 8 tbsp butter, melted; 2 eggs, large; 1 cup water. Yield: One 8 inch square pan. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Melt 8 tbsp butter. In bowl combine mix, sugar, melted butter, eggs and water. Pour into greased pan and bake for 23-25 minutes. Corn Muffins: Fill muffin tin 3/4 full. Bake for 15-17 minutes. Yield: 12 muffins. Variations: Sugar can be reduced or deleted for a less sweet cornbread. 1/4 cup honey or agave liquid can replace the sugar. 1/3 cup oil can replace the butter. Buttermilk Cornbread: Replace water with 1 cup buttermilk. Cheddar Cheese Cornbread: Add 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese. Green Chili Cheese Cornbread: Add 1 can (4 oz.) roasted green chili peppers, 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese, use unsalted butter, and add 1/4 cup additional water. Green Onion and Sour Cream: Add 1 cup sour cream, 1 cup chopped green onions and 1/2 tsp black pepper. Corn Kernel Corn Bread: Add 1 cup fresh or 1 can (8-3/4 oz.) canned corn kernels, drained. Optional, for color add 2 tbsp chopped pimentos. Sweet Pepper Cornbread: Reduce sugar to 2 tbsp and add 2 tbsp chopped red and yellow sweet peppers. Re-heat cornbread in microwave by wrapping in paper towels, or wrap in foil to re-heat in oven.
items.warnings: Allergen Information: Pamela's Products have been formulated and produced to be wheat-free and gluten-free. Our products are produced on equipment that also makes products containing tree nuts, soy, eggs, and milk.
items.ingredients: Organic Degermed Corn Meal, Brown Rice Flour, White Rice Flour, Tapioca Starch, Sweet Rice Flour, Potato Starch, Organic Degermed Corn Flour, Grainless & Aluminum Free Baking Powder (Sodium Bicarbonate, Sodium Acid Pyrophosphate, Potato Starch), Sea Salt, Xanthan Gum.

items.display_name: Cherrybrook Kitchen Sugar Cookie Mix Peanut Free!
items.directions: Here's how to make them! To make 20 cookies, all you need is: 1/2 cup melted margarine (substitute dairy free margarine or butter (unless you are allergic to this ingredient) according to your needs) + 1/4 cup rice milk (substitute plain soy milk or milk (unless you are allergic to this ingredient) according to your needs) + sugar cookie mix. 1. Heat oven to 350 degrees. 2. Stir margarine (substitute dairy free margarine or butter (unless you are allergic to this ingredient), rice milk (substitute plain soy milk or milk (unless you are allergic to this ingredient), and cookie mix at medium speed. 3. Roll the cookies into 1 inch balls and place them onto an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. 4. Bake 8-10 minutes or until they are a light golden brown. Cool 1 minute before removing from your cookie sheet. Cool completely before storing in an airtight container. 5. Enjoy!

items.name: Doughs, Gelatins & Bake Mixes Gluten Free Pantry French Bread Mix
items.display_name: Gluten Free Pantry French Bread Mix
items.directions: French Bread: Entire bag French Bread and Pizza Mix, enclosed packet of yeast (2-1/4 tsp). Combine: 1-3/4 cups lukewarm water or milk (you may adapt the recipe to suit your needs by using an equal amount of a substitute ingredient), 1 tsp cider vinegar, 1 tbsp honey or 1 tbsp sugar, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/3 cup vegetable oil, or melted butter (you may adapt the recipe to suit your needs by using an equal amount of a substitute ingredient), 2 eggs plus 1 egg white or 1 egg and 3 egg whites, lightly beaten (you may adapt the recipe to suit your needs by using an equal amount of a substitute ingredient). Large Bread Machine (2 lb capacity): Set machine on gluten free setting (follow manufacturer's direction for gluten-free setting). Short cycle and programmable features may be used. Follow manufacturers instructions for order of adding yeast, wet and dry ingredients. Press start. During first kneading cycle, open lid and use rubber spatula and help mix dough. If dough appears dry and crumbly, add warm water, 1 tbsp at a time, mixing after each addition, until dough is smooth and throughly moistened. For best results, remove baked bread immediately and cool on wire rack. For 1 lb bread machine, divide ingredients in half. Oven Method: Lightly oil a 9x5 inch loaf pan. Pour mix and yeast into large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and add. Beat 2 minutes using a heavy duty mixer. Scrape dough into loaf pan. Cover with plastic wrap. Let rise 40 minutes in a warm place or just until dough rises to the top of the pan. Brush with 1/4 tsp beaten egg. Preheat over to 375 degrees F (you may adapt the recipe to suit your needs by using an equal amount of a suitable ingredient). Bake 40-45 minutes or until golden and hollow-sounding when tapped. Turn onto rack. Cool completely. Slice, wrap, and freeze. Pizza: Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Prepare dough as in oven method. On lightly oiled cookie sheets or pizza pans spread dough desired thickness. Cover with favorite toppings. Bake 15 minutes or until edges of crust are brown.
items.ingredients: White Rice Flour, Potato Starch, Corn Starch, Guar Gum, Granulated Honey, Salt, and Packet of Yeast.
